Pretty alright. I have a few issues with it. With mastodon instances : No art/media only mode (the art tab is useless to me since you can't control what instances it displays); videos can't be set to repeat; it will only load 40 posts at a time instead of everything; when you mute someone, you have to restart the app to remove them from your timeline; if you try to mute someone while you have a poor mobile data connection , the app crashes immediately instead of just timing out.
Clunky and weird, but the best Mastodon app

I initially downloaded Tusky, but after finding out that it is amongst the Mastodon apps which block those they oppose politically, I refused to use it anymore as a matter of principle. Fedilab not only gives its users control over which communities they wish to be a part of, but also delivers all the functionality I'm looking for in my social media endeavors. Hats off to the developer.

Appreciate the app and the author's dedication to political neutrality. I personally use an instance which blocks the more controversial parts of the fediverse, but that blocking is done by the service with the community's (and my) implied support. This is not a service, it is software, in fact Free Software, which explicitly respects "freedom zero", the freedom to use the software for any purpose.
Opens a liberated world of sharing.

Enjoying it so far. I was still using the predecessor, Mastolab, until yesterday, this is much better. One feature suggestion: add an option to disable notifications for saving pictures. It's useless to me to be notified for that and it triggers the same notification I get for receiving a 'favorite' or comment, and since my custom notification sound for that is super loud and obnoxious, it gets old fast when I hear it every time I save a media file.
Easy to use and has a lot of features.

content: I had some issue opening the app, it turned out the app on the store changed (older app got removed, but new app retained the Purchased flag). App would just shut itself when I opened it. The store told me there was an update but download failed (because it tried to download the old app). Solution: Uninstall the old app, restart Google Play store if it still bugs out, then install the new app. You need to readd your Mastodon accounts, reenter your credentials, but it should work fine then.
replyContent: Oh thanks for the info. Many people reported that bug but I was not able to reproduce it on my end. I am keeping your solution in mind. Thank you.
